    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;The Point-to-Point Protocol (PPP) provides a standard method for transporting multi-protocol datagrams over point-to-point links.  PPP defines an extensible Link Control Protocol and a family of Network Control Protocols (NCPs) for establishing and configuring different network-layer protocols.  This memo provides information for the Internet community.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
